snippet.textDisplay:
200whp in an unopened NA engine.. That's high. Very high.. And brave, if you don't want to blow it up. But still. Wow, not bad. Those Ebay Turbos can actually be alright. I know many people running them, mostly modded or at least balanced by a pro. We even have a company where i live that offers those ebay turbos with a kit for RB25s and good for 400 (engine) hp. We measure with engine hp here.. Funny how so many countries have so many different ways to tell their power.



Edit: Well.. Should have waited until the end of the video. Not really surprising what happened, tough^^

snippet.textDisplay:
I once had a friend with a similar turbo car, also completely stock aside from the turbo install.
It made more or less the same amount of power, maybe differing by +-5hp.
expecting over 150hp of power after just the first tune was wishfull thinking.
It's a stock yaris, like come on.. be reasonable.
Getting over 100hp is amazing for a car like this, by just adding a turbo.

snippet.textDisplay: Kinda sad seeing the engine go, TRD used to sell a Supercharger kit for the older 1zz-fe 1.8l motors and those reliably made around 180-200~ hp from the standard motor, ECU and fuel system. They're also pretty reliable systems, i've seen cars that have had that kit for well over 100k km.
